Privacy Policy
Effective date:
March 4
, 2024
This Privacy Policy covers how we collect, use, disclose, transfer, and store your information. Please read this policy carefully to understand our practices regarding your information.
Your privacy and data security are extremely important to us. We are committed to the responsible management, protection, and use of your personal information.
Location Information:
When you use a location-enabled
Local Weather
service, we may automatically detect your general location to provide accurate weather information for your area. If you prefer, you can manually enter your location to obtain weather information.
Local File and Storage:
We utilize local shared objects to enhance your user experience, such as storing your city and weather data, user preferences, and settings.
Other information that we collect:
Information about your device and its capabilities
Your activities on the Services
Advertising identifiers
Referring URL
How do we use the information we collect?
We use the collected information to improve the features and experiences on our services. We also analyze our traffic. Additionally, we may share identifiers and other information from your device with our social media, advertising, and analytics partners. We do not sell, trade, or transfer your personally identifiable information to external parties, and we do not disclose your information.
Changes:
Our privacy policy may be updated periodically. We will not reduce your rights under this privacy policy without your explicit consent. Any changes to the privacy policy will be posted on this page, and significant changes will be prominently notified. Previous versions of the privacy policy will be archived for your reference.
If you have any questions or concerns about the Policy, you can contact us via email at: support@weather2024.com
